name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: We received a briefing on the security situation in Gaza, and also the activities of Hezbollah in Lebanon. We also visited an Iron Dome installation,  which protected Israel from the 4,000+ rockets launched by Hamas militants from Gaza in May 2021.  https://t.co/xq2K2cdWW1

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I had some great conversations with Fischel Ziegelheim while in Israel. He operates a kosher beef processing plant in Nebraska, but the company buys cattle from Iowa as well - including from my home area of Sioux County! Pictured here with Nebraska LG Mike Foley.  https://t.co/PmKWYQd0UV

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: While in Israel last week, I met the Governor of Binyamin Region, Mr. Israel Ganz (@israelganz). He was a very gracious host, and I look forward to returning soon!  https://t.co/kpcqf60T4W

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Israel is known as the Startup Nation, bursting with entrepreneurship and innovation. We heard from a number of startups with creative solutions for 911 services, constituent interaction, and traffic and road monitoring. @getnexar  @carbyne911  https://t.co/D8WdiRs9Hu

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Our delegation met with Benny Gantz (@gantzbe), Minister of Defense.  He's had a distinguished career as a general, the chief of staff of the IDF, and now a member of the Knesset and a key leader in the coalition government.  https://t.co/uav8jz9Kor

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: We had a great conversation with William @Daroff, CEO of the Conference of Presidents of Major American Jewish Organizations. He shared his experience helping Ukrainian refugees travel to Israel,  and encouraged our states to continue to build positive relationships with Israel.  https://t.co/zVOiRRk4cH

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: Iowa stands with our ally Israel, and we categorically reject anti-semitism. Thank you @IAGovernor and members of the legislature for getting this anti-BDS legislation signed. I am sending my pride and support from Jerusalem! 🇮🇱

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: We visited @UnitedHatzalah, a volunteer-based EMS service, with average response time of 3 minutes, with most under 90 seconds! Perhaps there are some concepts we can borrow for rural Iowa...🤔  https://t.co/Ss7RMzVMrO

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: While in Israel I've had a great meeting with Agriculture Minister @oded_forer. I've also met with representatives from the Volcani Institute, which is conducting research on post-harvest food waste together with Iowa State University (@IowaStateU).  https://t.co/Ja38T0q2Mn

name: Lt. Gov. Adam Gregg
tweet: I met with Kobi Bendelak (@KBendelak), CEO of InsurTech Israel. They and their affiliated startups have partnerships + investors in IA. Kobi told me he is bringing a group of 14 startup founders to IA next month for the Global Insurance Symposium. We look forward to hosting them!  https://t.co/EnI8Md2CWO
